🎭 Playwright Codegen – Simple Notes
📌 What is Codegen?

Codegen in Playwright is a feature that records your actions in the browser and converts them into automation code.

👉 It helps beginners quickly generate test scripts without writing everything manually.

🚀 How to Start Codegen
▶️ Basic Command
npx playwright codegen

👉 This will:

Open a browser
Start recording your actions
Generate code in real-time
🌐 Open Specific Website
npx playwright codegen https://example.com
🎯 Supported Browsers
npx playwright codegen --browser=chromium
npx playwright codegen --browser=firefox
npx playwright codegen --browser=webkit
🧠 How It Works
Run command
Browser opens
Perform actions (click, type, navigate)
Code is generated automatically

👉 Example:

await page.goto('https://example.com');
await page.click('text=Login');
await page.fill('#username', 'user1');
⚙️ Useful Options
📍 Save Script to File
npx playwright codegen -o test.spec.js
🌍 Set Viewport Size
npx playwright codegen --viewport-size=1280,720
🔐 Emulate Logged-in State
npx playwright codegen --storage-state=state.json
🎥 Record Video (during test run)
npx playwright test --video=on
💡 Best Practices

✔ Use Codegen only for initial script creation
✔ Refactor generated code (make it clean & reusable)
✔ Replace weak locators with strong ones (getByRole, getByText)
✔ Add assertions manually
✔ Follow Page Object Model (POM)